{"id":14881760,"mediaExerciseId":"fa4d8b42-30d1-45d6-aa1f-6c1ee163d0be","exerciseName":"2","chapterName":"21","chapterTitle":"International Corporate Finance","groupId":612470,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":735,"solutions":[{"id":5977730,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we will apply what we have learned about purchasing power parity.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/c4d8d018a4b2824d11eb7af806ebb6b4/1da759edd4b79694877dc82d0c7043fa/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/c4d8d018a4b2824d11eb7af806ebb6b4/1da759edd4b79694877dc82d0c7043fa/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"A **purchasing power parity** refers to the thought that the exchange rate adjusts in order to keep a constant purchasing power among the currencies. There are two forms of PPP, the absolute PPP and relative PPP.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/c4d8d018a4b2824d11eb7af806ebb6b4/a24c8c4580d9f7f589c860a4553f296e/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/c4d8d018a4b2824d11eb7af806ebb6b4/a24c8c4580d9f7f589c860a4553f296e/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"An **absolute purchasing power parity** refers to the concept of having a *same commodity cost* regardless of the currency used to purchase or sell it. If you have $1 that can buy you one Coca-Cola in US, absolute PPP indicates that you can also buy one Coca-Cola for $1 anywhere in the world.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/c4d8d018a4b2824d11eb7af806ebb6b4/04735e081470f4613aa9c8a7e3e73690/lateximg_large.png","width":1340},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/c4d8d018a4b2824d11eb7af806ebb6b4/04735e081470f4613aa9c8a7e3e73690/lateximg.png","width":669}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"A **relative purchasing power parity** refers to the concept that there is a *change in exchange rate* that can be determined by the *difference of the inflation rate* of two countries.  ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":100,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/c4d8d018a4b2824d11eb7af806ebb6b4/1235931ec8bc19d667d860dc493aa51d/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":51,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/c4d8d018a4b2824d11eb7af806ebb6b4/1235931ec8bc19d667d860dc493aa51d/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"In the exercise, the rate of inflation in Mexico will run about 3 percent higher than the U.S. inflation rate over the next several years. The **relative purchasing power parity** states that the change in exchange rate can be computed based on the difference in inflation rate of two countries.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/c4d8d018a4b2824d11eb7af806ebb6b4/2ad1f17894bf0299fd019d2347ad894f/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/02/c4d8d018a4b2824d11eb7af806ebb6b4/2ad1f17894bf0299fd019d2347ad894f/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"As a result, the **exchange rate** between Mexican Peso and U.S. Dollars will **increase by 3%**. It is determined based on the difference of the inflation rate of 3%.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"To sum it all up, the Mexican peso-U.S. dollar exchange rate will increase by 3% applying the concept of relative purchasing power.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"7b8a0271-0367-4368-8060-c824335d2d72","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":7}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881761,"exerciseName":"3","page":735,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"1970e93f-d5d8-48ef-83f5-aa53a6a6889b","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-critical-thinking-questions-3-1970e93f-d5d8-48ef-83f5-aa53a6a6889b"},{"id":14881762,"exerciseName":"4","page":735,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"f8ea0464-7797-427c-a01b-074c16ba668c","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-critical-thinking-questions-4-f8ea0464-7797-427c-a01b-074c16ba668c"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881759,"exerciseName":"1","p